Product: Clinora

Version: 1.0

Document Type: High-Level System Architecture (HLD)

Audience: Architects, Backend Developers, Frontend Developers, DevOps Engineers, QA, Product Team

1. Purpose

The purpose of this document is to define the high-level technical architecture of the Clinora platform.

It provides a technology-agnostic view of how users, applications, services, databases, and integrations interact to deliver the core healthcare workflows.

This document acts as the architectural blueprint that guides application development while remaining independent of specific cloud infrastructure decisions.

2. Architecture Goals

The architecture is designed to achieve the following objectives:

Modular and maintainable design
Multi-tenant SaaS architecture
Secure patient data isolation
Scalable cloud-native deployment
High availability
Responsive user experience
Reliable background processing
Easy integration with third-party healthcare services
Support future AI capabilities
3. Architectural Principles

Clinora follows these architectural principles:

Modular Design

Business capabilities are divided into independent modules.

API-First

All communication between frontend and backend occurs through REST APIs.

Stateless Services

Application servers do not store session state.

Multi-Tenant by Design

Every request belongs to a tenant (clinic).

Event-Driven Processing

Long-running operations execute asynchronously.

Security First

Authentication, authorization, audit logging, and encryption are enforced throughout the platform.

